Janiszewo  is a settlement in the administrative district of Gmina Sorkwity, within Mrągowo County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-west of Sorkwity,  west of Mrągowo, and  east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
